Data Wrangling¶

Introduction¶

In this project, I will be analyzing the tweet archive of Twitter user @dog_rates, also known as WeRateDogs. WeRateDogs is a Twitter account that rates people's dogs with a humorous comment about the dog. Using Python and its libraries, I will gather data from a variety of sources and in a variety of formats, assess its quality and tidiness, then clean it.

tweet_list =tw_df['tweet_id']
consumer_key = 'XXXXX'
consumer_secret = 'XXXXX'
access_token = 'XXXXX'
access_secret = 'XXXXX'

auth = tweepy.OAuthHandler(consumer_key, consumer_secret)
auth.set_access_token(access_token, access_secret)

api = tweepy.API(auth,wait_on_rate_limit=True,wait_on_rate_limit_notify=True)
In [11]:
#extract data from API and store it in text file
tweet_list =tw_df['tweet_id']
broken_link=[]

start_time=time.process_time()
with open('tweet_json.txt', 'w') as json_file:
    for tweet_id in tweet_list:
        try:
            tweet_status=api.get_status(tweet_id, tweet_mode='extended')
            json.dump(tweet_status._json,json_file)
            json_file.write('\n')
        except Exception as e:
            print(e)
            broken_link.append(tweet_id)
end_time=time.process_time()
print(broken_link)
print(end_time-start_time)

#Extract favorite count, retweet count from the json text file and load it into a data frame
tweet_ids=[]
fav_count=[]
retweet_count=[]
retweeted=[]
with open('tweet_json.txt') as tweet_file: 
    for line in tweet_file:
        
        json_data = json.loads(line)
        tweet_ids.append(json_data['id'])
        retweet_count.append(json_data['retweet_count'])
        fav_count.append(json_data['favorite_count'])
        
tw_count_df=pd.DataFrame({'tweet_id':tweet_ids,'favorite_count':fav_count,'retweet_count':retweet_count})

Based on the visual and programmatic assesments above, the following issues have been identified.

Quality¶

Twitter archive dataset¶

  • Duplicates: There are some tweets that are retweets/duplicates of the original tweets
  • Missing data: There are few entries that are missing image urls.
  • Accuracy: Some dog names are incorrect like 'a'.'an' etc
  • Incorrect datatype : in_reply_to_status_id, in_reply_to_user_id, retweeted_status_id, retweeted_status_user_id are of data type float
  • Incorrect datatype: timestamp, retweeted_status_timestamp are of datatype String.
  • Accuracy: Some ratings are incorrect such as 450/500,24/7 etc. Some of the ratings are for group of dogs and some are parsing errors.

Image predictions dataset¶

  • Some values in dog prediction columns p1,p2,p3 have underscores. Eg border_collie
  • Ambiguity: The column names p1,p2,p3,p1_conf,p2_conf and p3_conf are not intuitive

Tidiness¶

  • Dog stages doggo,floofer,pupper and puppo can be combined to a single column.
  • Three separate datasets are not required. The datasets can be merged.

Cleaning data¶

In this section, I will fix the issues identified int the previous section.

Prior to cleaning the data, I will make a copy of the dataset.

In [145]:
# copy dataset into another dataframe.
tw_clean=tw_df.copy()
image_clean=image_df.copy()
tw_count_clean=tw_count_df.copy()

Quality Issues¶

Define¶

  • Remove retweets from twitter archive dataset

Code¶

In [146]:
#Remove records that have been retweeted
tw_clean=tw_clean[tw_clean['retweeted_status_id'].isna()]

Test¶

In [147]:
#check for count of retweets
tw_clean[~tw_clean['retweeted_status_id'].isna()].retweeted_status_id.count()

In [148]:
# Exclude records without expanded_urls
tw_clean=tw_clean[~tw_clean['expanded_urls'].isna()]

tw_clean[tw_clean['expanded_urls'].isna()].expanded_urls.count()

  • Fix ratings of tweets consistent with WeRatedogs rating system.
    • Convert the denominator of the ratings to a scale of 10
    • Fix numerator values based on group dog ratings and parsing errors.
    • Remove tweets that dont have valid rating.

It can be seen that rating numerator that are greater than 10 for 2 reasons

  • The tweet is a picture of group of dogs Eg: 45/50 is the composite rating for 5 puppies
  • The rating is a parsing error from the text field
In [160]:
#Fix the denominator and numerator of cases of  group dog tweets and parsing errors
group_dog_denominator=[]
for tw_id in tw_clean[tw_clean['rating_denominator']>10].tweet_id:
    #Cases where denominator isa multiple of 10 - group dogs
    # Normalize ratings to a scale of 10
    if(tw_clean.rating_denominator[tw_clean['tweet_id']==tw_id].values[0]%10==0):
        tw_clean.rating_numerator[tw_clean['tweet_id']==tw_id]= tw_clean.rating_numerator[tw_clean['tweet_id']==tw_id].values[0] * 10/tw_clean.rating_denominator[tw_clean['tweet_id']==tw_id].values[0]
        tw_clean.rating_denominator[tw_clean['tweet_id']==tw_id]=10
    #cases where the ratings are a parsing error
    # Extract rating from text field
    else:
        tw_clean.rating_numerator[tw_clean['tweet_id']==tw_id]= tw_clean.text[tw_clean['tweet_id']==tw_id].values[0].split("/10")[-2].split()[-1]
        tw_clean.rating_denominator[tw_clean['tweet_id']==tw_id]=10
tw_clean.rating_numerator=np.int64(tw_clean.rating_numerator)
In [161]:
#Remove records that have no ratings and/or is a fundraising post
invalid_record=tw_clean[~tw_clean['text'].str.contains("/10") & tw_clean['expanded_urls'].str.contains("gofundme")].index.values
tw_clean=tw_clean.drop(invalid_record)
In [162]:
#Numerator rating of 14 is the highest. 
#However some records have high values. Extract correct values by parsing the text description
for tw_id in tw_clean[tw_clean['rating_numerator']>14].tweet_id:
     tw_clean.rating_numerator[tw_clean['tweet_id']==tw_id]=tw_clean.text[tw_clean['tweet_id']==tw_id].values[0].split("/10")[-2].split()[-1]
tw_clean.rating_numerator=tw_clean.rating_numerator.astype(float)

Define¶

  • Remove underscores in prediction fields

Code¶

In [168]:
for tw_id in image_clean.tweet_id:
    image_pred1= image_clean.prediction1[image_clean['tweet_id']==tw_id]
    image_pred2= image_clean.prediction2[image_clean['tweet_id']==tw_id]
    image_pred3= image_clean.prediction3[image_clean['tweet_id']==tw_id]

    if "_" in image_pred1.values[0]:
        image_clean.prediction1[image_clean['tweet_id']==tw_id]=image_pred1.values[0].replace("_"," ") 
    if "_" in image_pred2.values[0]:
        image_clean.prediction2[image_clean['tweet_id']==tw_id]=image_pred2.values[0].replace("_"," ")

Observations¶

  • The mean rating is 11.63. The highest is 1776 which corresponds to a humorous tweet.
  • The machine learning predictions seemed to perform better in Prediction one with a higher mean of confidence rate - 0.598
  • The maximum number of times a tweet was favorited was 143578 times
  • The maximum number of retweets are 77476
